BOB BENDER of Illinois State was hired Friday as the men's basketball at the University of Washington. Bender, Illinois State's coach for four years, replaces LYNN NANCE, who resigned March 19. Athletic director BARBARA HEDGES said Bender will be given a long-term contract, probably four years, at $110,000 a season. Bender, 35, was an assistant under MIKE KRZYZEWSKI at Duke for six years before taking over at Illinois State. In four years as coach of the Redbirds, his teams won two Missouri Valley Conference regular-season titles and made one National Collegiate Athletic Association tournament appearance. (AP)
